'''①计划'''（{{lang-ja|マル1計画，第一次補充計画}}）是[[大日本帝国海軍|大日本帝国海軍]]的一项海軍軍備计划。正式名称为'''第一次補充计划'''，通常在〇中嵌入数字1，称为丸一（まるいち）计划。是在[[伦敦海军条约|伦敦海軍軍縮条約]]締結之后，为应对条约限制所提出的首轮建舰计划。

==背景==
《[[伦敦海军条约|伦敦海军条约]]》在大型军舰的吨位和数量方面比对[[美国海军|美国海军]]和[[英国皇家海军|英国皇家海军]]对日本的海军能力进行了严格限制<ref>Evans, ''Kaigun''. page 238-239</ref>。

①计划在1930年11月由日本[[海军省|日本海军省]]提交[[日本內閣|内阁]]批准，<!--The "Circle One" plan was submitted by the [[Ministry_of_the_Navy_of_Japan|Naval Ministry]] and approved by the [[Cabinet_of_Japan|Cabinet]] in November 1930, -->并于1931年被[[國會_(日本)|日本国会]]正式通过。<!--and officially ratified by the [[Diet_of_Japan|Diet of Japan]] in 1931. It called for the construction of 39 new combat vessels, centering around four of the new [[Mogami_class_cruiser|''Mogami''-class]] [[cruiser|cruiser]]s, and expansion of the [[Imperial_Japanese_Navy_Air_Service|Imperial Japanese Navy Air Service]] to 14 Naval Air Groups. Budget for the construction of the warships was on a six-year basis, and the budget for forming the air groups was on a three-year basis. Total funding allotted was 247,080,000 [[Yen|Yen]] for ship construction and 44,956,000 Yen for naval aviation expansion.

In terms of naval aviation development, the "Circle One" plan also concentrated on the development of new aircraft technologies, especially large [[seaplane|seaplane]]s, land-based [[bomber|bomber]]s, as well as carrier-based [[attack_aircraft|attack aircraft]] and [[floatplane|floatplane]] attack aircraft that could be launched from [[battleship|battleship]]s, cruisers or submarines. Attention was also given to training of pilots and air crews in [[dive_bombing|dive bombing]] and [[torpedo|torpedo]] [[Military_tactics|tactics]]. <ref>Evans, ''Kaigun'', age 249</ref>  

In a 1932 supplement to the Circle One plan, additional funding was added for the construction of three more vessels: the [[submarine_tender|submarine tender]] [[Japanese_aircraft_carrier_Ryūhō|''Taigei'']], and two [[submarine_chaser|submarine chaser]]s.-->

